message.entry: The second input has to be a non-negative integer.
The first argument has to be a scalar or a vector.
K must be an integer between 0 and N.
When N is single or double, its maximum allowed value is FLINTMAX.
Integers can only be combined with integers of the same class, or scalar doubles.
Result may not be exact. Coefficient has a maximum relative error of {0}, corresponding to absolute error {1}.
